<br>
No it's not your fault the calendar is messed up, nor is it your fault the full message of the calendar being down was on another board.  But it is your fault for not seeing the posts on THIS board that stated the calendar was down (in the title part even) and not investigating.  It is your fault for not looking into the calendar being down when you discovered it, or even putting forth the question on these boards as to why to calendar was down.  And it is your fault for not reading the rules before scheduling a raid.  When you originally decided to make this raid...the calendar was up and the rules were available for you to read.  If you had followed them none of this would have happened.  When you know you need to do a thing as soon as possible, and discover you can't...you don't walk away assuming everything is okay.  You do what you can to get what you want done.   It is not up to others to do for you, it is up to you to do for yourself. <br>
<br>
A story:  A friend of mine wanted to raid in PoF (might have been PoH but that's not important) he scheduled it too early having not read the rule.  He was informed he scheduled it wrong, and before he could schedule again within the 2 week timeframe, someone else had it scheduled.  He didn't tell that person they were trying to &quot;gank&quot; because they &quot;knew&quot; he wanted that day.  He shrugged it off and rescheduled for another date.  Because he knew he made a mistake.  There are consequences you must expect when you don't follow the rules.  And one of the consequences is that someone else may get the date you wanted.  Do the adult thing, shrug it off and  reschedule properly.<br>
<br>
Grimina<br>
